rComments: Professor Kee is very knowledgeable in the course material. She constantly checks to see if students follow her and tries her best to provide good learning environment. She cares about the students' success and holds extra office hours. She may be a little confusing during her lectures but is very helpful during her office hours.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Prof Kee is a good lecturer and she is very welcoming to questions from the class. She's sometimes funny and very passionate about her subject. She's excellent in office hours too. That's where her teaching skills shine as she can almost immediately see where you're confused and explain what you're unclear on.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: By the book professor, no life in the lectures. I don't think she fully and deeply understood the topics she was talking about.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She was very unclear. She expected us to know a lot that we never learned in the prereq course. Her lectures were hard to follow, and the homework was very long and didn't seem to relate. The textbook was BAD, and she confused us all by basically switching textbooks halfway through the course.
Talks at light speed with an accent, gets very impatient during class, and tests are fair but marked hard (few part marks)
